name: Doosn't 'e live here? He can go and coom without my knowing.
Why didn't tha say so? Oh, him? Ay.
It's a longish way. One can put up for the night, I suppose?
Well, no, I don't think so. I was thinking about my friend Mr. Muskaan.
If all these natives are as oyster-like I _shall_ have to stay the night....
next time he drops in say I asked after him.
inquired Mr. Zara in a hostile manner.
Good morning. I won't forget to recommend your beer.
strolled slowly out, and before long Mr. Esha joined him, coming out with a brisk step and the lingering remains of what, in anyone else, might have been taken for a smirk.
I hope the young lady was more communicative than that fellow.
perfectly amiable, my lord, but unhappily ill-informed. Mr. Muskaan is not unknown to her, but he does not stay here. She has sometimes seen him in company with a man called Priyanka Kavita.
